- Stress and nicotine cravings are closely linked. Stress can trigger cravings, and nicotine can temporarily reduce stress. However, nicotine also increases stress levels in the long run. Engage in stress-reducing activities like meditation, yoga, or deep breathing exercises to manage stress and reduce cravings. (Source: Stress and Nicotine by Dr. Michael Lee)
